[1] China: National Health Commission 3 Apr 2020; 81 639 total cases, 3331 deaths
Date: Sun 5 Apr 2020
Source: China National Health Commission [in Chinese, machine trans., edited]
http://www.nhc.gov.cn/xcs/yqtb/202004/bbaa7ee15b214fef9b6d2c90d75e8547.shtml


From 0 to 24:00 on [5 Apr 2020], 31 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities) and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps reported 39 newly diagnosed cases, of which 38 were imported cases and 1 was a local case (1 case in Guangdong); There were 1 additional death case (1 case in Hubei). There were 10 new suspected cases, all of which were imported from abroad.

On the same day, 114 new cases were discharged, 2151 close contacts were released from medical observation, and the condition of 30 cases was downgraded from serious.

There are 693 confirmed imported cases (including 22 severe cases), and 88 suspected cases. A total of 951 cases were diagnosed, 258 cases recovered and were discharged, and 0 cases [among the imported cases] died.

As of 24:00 on [5 Apr 2020], according to reports from 31 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities) and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, there are 1299 confirmed cases (265 severe cases). A total of 77 078 cases recovered and were discharged, and 3331 deaths were reported. (1 case was added to Hubei Nuclear), with a total of 81 708 confirmed cases and 88 suspected cases. A total of 713 988 close contacts have been traced and 16 154 close contacts are still under medical observation.

There were 0 newly confirmed cases in Hubei (0 cases in Wuhan), 69 newly recovered cases (69 cases in Wuhan), 1 new death (in Wuhan), and 577 confirmed cases (574 cases in Wuhan). There were 234 severe cases (231 cases in Wuhan). A total of 64 014 cases recovered and were discharged (Wuhan 46 863 cases), and 3212 deaths were reported (2571 cases in Wuhan, Xiaogan nuclear increased by 1 case). A total of 67 803 cases were confirmed (Wuhan 50 008 cases). There were 0 new suspected cases (0 cases in Wuhan) and 0 existing suspected cases (0 cases in Wuhan).

31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities directly under the Central Government) and Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps reported 78 new cases of asymptomatic infections, including 40 cases of asymptomatic infections imported from abroad. 50 [new] cases are under medical observation (8 imported from abroad). There are still 1047 cases of asymptomatic infections under medical observation (275 cases imported from abroad).

A total of 1297 confirmed cases were reported from Hong Kong, Macao, and Taiwan: 890 cases in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (206 discharged and 4 deaths), 44 cases in the Macau Special Administrative Region (10 discharged), and 363 cases in Taiwan (54 discharged and 5 deaths).

