[It is now 2 days since the last report of a locally transmitted case in Wuhan. Of concern is the local transmission ongoing in Guangdong. Yesterday (4 Apr 2020), there were 5 newly confirmed cases reported in Guangdong, today (5 Apr 2020), there is 1 additional case reported from Guangdong. At the country level there were 39 newly confirmed cases reported of which 38 were imported cases.

According to the report above, a total of 81 708 cases of confirmed COVID-19 have now been reported from mainland China, including 3331 deaths, representing an increase of 39 cases in the 24 hours since yesterday's (4 Apr 2020) report was prepared. An additional 10 suspected cases were newly reported, all imported cases. In addition, 1 death was reported, from Wuhan. 28 new cases were reported from Hong Kong, where numbers of newly confirmed cases continue to increase daily. And Macau has reported 0 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours.

A total of 38 newly confirmed cases were imported cases into China. Origins of importation were not available but the total number of imported cases is now 951. There are an additional 88 suspected imported cases. Clearly the challenge for China now is the identification of infections in imported cases, tracing their contacts, and preventing the recurrence of community wide transmission.

As best as I can decipher from the report above, there were 78 newly confirmed infections in asymptomatic people in the past 24 hours, 40 in imported cases. The total number of asymptomatic individuals currently under observation (and isolation) is 1047, 275 of whom are importations from abroad. 5 originally asymptomatic cases have developed symptoms in the past 24 hours (all were imported cases).

As reported on 24 Mar 2020, China ended the lockdown in Hubei and will end it in Wuhan tomorrow on 6 Apr 2020. There is much caution and skepticism in the media over the reality of the zero case reports. The world will be watching carefully to see if this is safe timing...

A map of China showing provinces can be seen at https://www.chinadiscovery.com/china-maps/china-provincial-map.html and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map is available at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7189083,155. - Mod.MPP]

