[Transmission of the SARS-CoV-2 in Spain appears to be leveling off and beginning a decrease. That being said, Spain is now 2nd globally in terms of number of confirmed cases of COVID-19, having surpassed Italy. From a high of 9222 cases reported in 24 hours on 31 Mar 2020, there has been a gradual decline in daily cases reported so that today's report shows a 34.7% reduction since 31 Mar 2020. As of today (5 Apr 2020), totals of 130 759 cases and 12 418 deaths have been reported, up from 124 736 cases and 11 744 deaths confirmed in the preceding 24 hours. The countrywide 2-week incidence per 100 000 population is now 217.3. It is 2nd in Europe, behind Italy, and 3rd globally behind the USA and Italy, in terms of absolute numbers of cases. Figure 1 at the source URL above shows the daily confirmations juxtaposed with dates of onset of disease and one clearly sees the trend for increasing confirmations in recent times. There is also a clear growth curve showing the trajectory of the epidemic at https://covid19.isciii.es/; it is updated daily.

Of the 130 759 cases, 58 744 (44.9%) have been hospitalized and 6861 (5.2%) admitted to the ICU. The crude reported case fatality rate is 9.5%, with more deaths occurring than reported ICU admissions. Both the proportion of cases hospitalized and the proportion of cases in ICU have shown slight decreases over the past few days.

A map of Spain showing provinces (autonomous communities) can be seen at https://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/spain-administrative-map.htm and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7189083,43. La Rioja, Navarre, and Basque Country are located together in the north of the country. Madrid is in the northern part of central Spain and Castile-La Mancha is just to the south of Madrid, with Toledo as its capital. - Mod.MPP]

******
[7] Turkey, cumulative case counts increasing rapidly
Date: Sat 4 Apr 2020
Source: Assume Tech [edited]
https://asumetech.com/why-turkey-is-facing-a-steep-curve-of-new-coronavirus-cases/


Considering that stating its 1st coronavirus case 3 weeks back, Turkey has actually tape-recorded one of the steepest trajectories of new cases on the planet, in the middle of worries it might end up being a location of the pandemic. The fast rise in cases -- 18 135 validated infections and 356 deaths as of late Thursday [2 Apr 2020] -- has actually seen Turkey surpass other G20 states such as South Korea and Canada that reported cases of the infection weeks previously.

It has actually likewise left Turks asking if the nation may be following the course of Italy, which has actually tape-recorded more than 110 000 cases. "Turkey has the highest acceleration rate for cases," stated Caghan Kizil, associate teacher of neuroscience and genes at the Helmholtz Association of German Research Study Centres.

"This is because social mobility wasn't prevented. If we look at China, they were successful because they identified asymptomatic patients who weren't showing signs of infection. After the lockdown in Wuhan, the number of cases caused by undocumented infected people dropped significantly." Esin Senol, a teacher of transmittable illness at Gazi University in Ankara, mentioned that Turkey has actually now seen the world's 10th-highest number of cases and is one of the countries at many danger.

"It appears to have spread long before the 1st case was reported, due to trips to Europe, Iran, and Umrah," she stated, describing the Muslim expedition to Saudi Arabia. Restricting screening to those who had actually just recently been abroad in the early days of the break out in Turkey likewise enabled the infection to spread out, Senol added.

On Thursday night [2 Apr 2020], Minister of Health Fahrettin Koca revealed 79 new deaths. The figure is far lower than numbers seen in the worst days in countries like Italy and Spain, where day-to-day death tolls have actually regularly exceeded 800 just recently, it was the sharpest boost yet in Turkey. In an interview on Wednesday [1 Apr 2020], Koca exposed for the 1st time the nature of the spread of the break out throughout Turkey, revealing that 60 percent of cases had actually been reported in Istanbul, the nation's industrial center, which represents a 5th of Turkey's population.

Mehmet Ceyhan, chairman of Turkey's Contagious Diseases Association, cautioned that the nation might see its number of infections overtake others. "If we go at the current rate, our number of cases will be 300 000 in 10 days," he stated. Nevertheless, shutting down public areas, limiting travel in between cities and guaranteeing people remain at home would prevent such a remarkable situation.

"I look at the measures that have been implemented, and our people have begun to adapt a little better," Ceyhan stated. "If we comply with the measures in the same way, we may see a fall in the rate of increase."

Scarcities
----------
In spite of winning appreciation for its early adoption of constraints such as border closures, suspending flights, and quarantining those aged over 65, the federal government has actually dealt with criticism over the reasonably low number of tests performed. Turkey had actually carried out simply under 107 000 tests and just reached a target of performing 10 000 a day on Monday [30 Mar 2020]. This compares to more than half a million tests performed in Italy.

Expert medical groups have actually highlighted a shortage in the equipment, beds and health personnel required to handle bigger numbers of coronavirus clients. "It is evident that hospitals in the city have not prepared adequately in the 2.5 months since this deadly virus first came into the spotlight," the Istanbul Chamber of Physicians stated in a declaration. In addition to a lack of protective equipment such as masks and gloves, the chamber likewise criticised an absence of organisation and incorrect screening of health employees, keeping in mind that more than 100 personnel in Istanbul medical facilities had actually checked favorable.

According to the federal government, more than 600 healthcare personnel have actually been contaminated throughout Turkey. "That's worrying," stated Kizil. "The answer to the question of whether we will be like Italy will be determined by how ready our healthcare system is for the high number of cases that appear on the horizon."

Require quarantine
------------------
Ankara has actually withstood requiring a full lockdown, with President Recep Tayyip Erdogan requiring services to remain open and keep the economy's "wheels turning." Nevertheless, the president stated Turkey would step up procedures if the break out continued dispersing.

The federal government has actually advised people to remain at home; closed bars, coffee shops, and schools; limited domestic travel; stopped international flights; and suspended sporting occasions and spiritual events. The presidency declined to comment on the effectiveness of its procedures, however Koca on Wednesday [1 Apr 2020] safeguarded the federal government's action and stated the health ministry intended to execute 30 000 tests daily within 10 days.

[Byline: Dianna Clary]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[I have been flagging the rapid increase in confirmed cases in Turkey over the past week or so as it has been climbing up the ladder of ranking order among the global arena. In a little more than 3 weeks, it is now number 9 globally.

Reading the descriptions of the challenges is a déjà vu of reading the challenges experienced in Italy and the United States. Basically a lack of preparedness for dealing with pandemic surge capacity needs.

A map of Turkey showing administrative divisions can be found at https://www.mapsofworld.com/turkey/turkey-political-map.html and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7189083,87. - Mod.MPP]
